claim.claim-text:
1. Neck leash device for retaining eye wear comprising: 
a resilient leash or strap portion approximately thirty four inches long; 
a pair of adjustment beads, one for adjusting the leash around the users neck and the other for adjusting the leash around the users head; 
a leash to eyeglass attachment means; 
said attachment means comprised of a length of resilient tubing terminating at one end in a first plastic fastener, said opposite end capable of retaining the ear piece of a pair of glasses; 
and a mating second plastic fastener that attaches to each end of said leash portion, said mating first and second fasteners comprised of resilient plastic material so that they can snap together and detach from each other in an emergency.
